Package: mctaus
Title: Australian Multivariate Core Trend Inflation
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("David", "Stephan", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Bayesian dynamic factor model for Australian CPI sub-groups,
    producing a measure of trend inflation and a decomposition of where
    persistence is coming from (common vs sector-specific). An Australian
    analogue of the NY Fed's Multivariate Core Trend (MCT) inflation
    model. Estimation by a custom Gibbs sampler (port of the NY Fed
    MATLAB sampler); orchestration via targets; dashboard via Quarto.
